cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper discusses the representation of ontologies in a first-order logical environment, which is closely related to database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of formal axioms to constrain the interpretation of primitives, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the transformational passage from the classification form of first-order logic to an equivalent interpretation form, which is relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
